00:01:00.160 --> 00:01:04.730
So take a quick moment to read
over that while I describe

00:01:04.730 --> 00:01:07.200
the overall flow of the course.

00:01:07.200 --> 00:01:10.020
The course roadmap, this
little diagram right here,

00:01:10.020 --> 00:01:12.290
is essentially a
three step component.

00:01:12.290 --> 00:01:14.820
We first instill
the fundamentals

00:01:14.820 --> 00:01:17.540
of how light is absorbed
into a material, how charge

00:01:17.540 --> 00:01:19.612
is excited, how then
charge is separated

00:01:19.612 --> 00:01:21.070
and a voltage
created, and finally,

00:01:21.070 --> 00:01:22.720
how a charge is collected.

00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:25.700
And that is the essence
of a photovoltaic device.

00:01:25.700 --> 00:01:28.690
In 30 years time,
photovoltaic devices

00:01:28.690 --> 00:01:31.930
probably will still be
using that combination

00:01:31.930 --> 00:01:33.360
of physical processes.

00:01:33.360 --> 00:01:35.230
So understanding
these fundamentals

00:01:35.230 --> 00:01:38.670
will arm you-- will give
you the information needed

00:01:38.670 --> 00:01:41.250
to be able to assess any
photovoltaic technology that

00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:43.490
might be presented to you.

00:01:43.490 --> 00:01:46.300
Then, in the second
component of the course,

00:01:46.300 --> 00:01:48.890
we'll discuss the technologies,
the specific technologies that

00:01:48.890 --> 00:01:50.390
are out there in
the market today,

00:01:50.390 --> 00:01:53.140
and those that are up and
coming that have the potential

00:01:53.140 --> 00:01:54.470
to replace them.

00:01:54.470 --> 00:01:56.330
And as a third
part of the course,

00:01:56.330 --> 00:01:58.130
we'll be discussing
cross cutting themes.

00:01:58.130 --> 00:02:02.130
These include the policy,
economics, and social aspects

00:02:02.130 --> 00:02:05.080
of photovoltaics that, of
course, are of general interest

00:02:05.080 --> 00:02:07.740
and are particularly interesting
for scientists and engineers,

00:02:07.740 --> 00:02:08.990
who spend most of
their time thinking

00:02:08.990 --> 00:02:11.156
about the fundamentals, to
take a step back and look

00:02:11.156 --> 00:02:13.720
at the broader picture.

